Almost 17,000 Ghanaians Evacuated From Libya, Ghana News Says

-- B y   J a s o n   M c L u r e
-- 
2011-03-23T09:23:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-23/almost-17-000-ghanaians-evacuated-from-libya-ghana-news-says.html
A total of 16,822 Ghanaians have
been evacuated from  Libya  and another 900 remain in the country
waiting to escape from its month-old civil war, the  Ghana  News
Agency reported.  Among the evacuees are 90 prisoners freed from Libyan
jails, including eight former death row inmates, the state-owned
news service said, citing Muhammad Mumuni, Ghanaâ€™s foreign
